17:
And thanks for grabbing that one for
me.
20:
No problem—looks like I got here just
in time.
23:
...Did you bring all these Shroombos
here?
32:
Now just what have we walked into
here?
37:
Couette's powers have been getting
stronger recently.
41:
If I'm not careful, my dreams spill out
into the real world...
45:
...I would surmise this is due to you
visiting different worlds. Your
ever-expanding understanding has
outpaced your consciousness.
49: How can I help it catch up?
53:
...Heh. By getting tutelage from the
right people—which we can offer, if
you'd like.
60:
Ta-da! I'm all dressed up for the
Diviners' Commission.
63: Oh, wow! It's a very cool outfit.
87:
Is it just me or does Koma look
different too?
93:
Yeah. I'm not really sure when it
happened, but that's what Koma
looks like now.
98:
Huh...
Well, I guess we don't entirely know
what Koma is, after all...
100:
But I'm glad everything's all right. I
guess your studies with the Diviners'
Commission are going well?
105:
Yup. It's just like going to school! It's
really fun.
108:
Mizuchi and Kugui are also really
nice to me...
115:
Hehehe! I'll study everything I can
here!
127:
Wonderful. You've made exceptional
progress in such a short time.
135:
...But I still don't know how to use my
own powers to their full potential.
139:
That won't be a problem. Gaining
mastery over a magical form
different from your own should help
you—
142:
My, is that the girl? The one invited
here from another world by the
Chair of the Diviners' Commission?
143:
They say she can perform magical
arts not bound by our fundamental
principles, but I disagree—she is only
capable of gawdy parlor tricks!
144:
If he has the time to watch this girl
perform trite illusions, surely he
could afford us a moment or two!
147: I'm sorry... It's my fault that they—
150:
Nonsense. You haven't done
anything wrong, Couette. I have
simply been too preoccupied to
attend to everyone.
153:
Hmm... I believe I have an idea what
to do.
156:
One which will allow us to disabuse
them of their narrow
preconceptions.
161:
Chairman, you've got that look
again...
164:
Pray tell, Chairman... For what
reason have you summoned us all
here?
167:
Suizen, is it really okay for me to go
all-out?
170:
Of course. It's only in pushing our
limits that we can truly know them.
I've no doubt this will help you learn
to control your power.
174:
Don't worry, Couette. This area is
apparently very sealed-off.
176:
We'll be here for you even if things
go wrong. So just give it everything
you've got!
195:
Study though we may, there are
molds into which we cannot fit. The
essential principles of divining go
against your fundamental nature.
198:
But that does not mean they cannot
act as guideposts to light your way
in the encroaching dark.
201:
Come, Couette. Harness the
principles of divining, and use them
as stepping stones to walk through
the darkness!
222: You did it! Great work, Couette.
225: Heehee. That was satisfying to do.
229:
And I think I learned something
about myself.
232:
Impossible... Her deeds flout every
precept we hold to be true! And yet...
Gah, I do not understand!
233:
This utterly defies our understanding
of the five elements! What cosmic
forces does this girl control?!
235:
Chairman! Is this what you wanted
to show us?!
237: Girl! Show us again! I beg of you!
243:
She turned everything they knew
about magic upside down, huh?
Maybe this was a little overboard.
246:
Such are the consequences of one's
actions. Couette was simply the
messenger.
249:
If it's compensation you want, we'll
give you anything! Knowledge?
Magical techniques? Candy?
256:
...In that case, I'd like you to teach
me all kinds of things!
258:
One day, I'm gonna be the best
mage ever!
